  <div class="article-wrap">
    <div class="body-text">

      <p>This is a book-length version of the argument made across five series and eleven thinker profiles on this site. It is not a collection of the existing articles — it is a reworking of that material into a single sustained argument, with new connecting tissue, expanded chapters, and a linear structure designed for reading start to finish.</p>

      <p>It is being written in public. Chapters will appear here as they are drafted. The outline is the current state of the architecture.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>Structure</h2>

      <p><strong>Prologue: One Pattern</strong> — The argument in miniature. What connects the rent, the highway, the hospital, the platform.</p>

      <h3>Part I: The Machine</h3>
      <p>Why the system produces the same outcomes regardless of who runs it.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Chapter 1: Why Your City Doesn't Work</li>
        <li>Chapter 2: Who Captures the Value</li>
        <li>Chapter 3: The Commons Works</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Part II: The Hidden Engine</h3>
      <p>What capitalism extracts, and from whom.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Chapter 4: The Outside</li>
        <li>Chapter 5: How the Outside Gets Made</li>
        <li>Chapter 6: What They Burned</li>
        <li>Chapter 7: Abolition Is a Presence, Not an Absence</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Part III: What the Left Got Wrong</h3>
      <p>The diagnosis was correct. The prescription was not.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Chapter 8: They Were Right About the Problem</li>
        <li>Chapter 9: The Party Ate the Revolution</li>
        <li>Chapter 10: The Tradition They Buried</li>
        <li>Chapter 11: Build It Now</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Part IV: What the Framework Missed</h3>
      <p>What the colonized already knew.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Chapter 12: Race Was Always There</li>
        <li>Chapter 13: The Colony in the Mind</li>
        <li>Chapter 14: Building Anyway</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Part V: What to Build</h3>
      <p>The preparation is already underway.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Chapter 15: The Choice Available Now</li>
        <li>Chapter 16: Credit</li>
        <li>Chapter 17: Land</li>
        <li>Chapter 18: Care</li>
        <li>Chapter 19: Knowledge and Language</li>
        <li>Chapter 20: What's Being Built</li>
        <li>Chapter 21: The Agent and the Commons</li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>Epilogue: The Commons Is Not What Was Taken</strong></p>

      <hr />

      <p style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.75rem;opacity:0.5">
        Estimated 59,000 words across 23 chapters + thinker profiles. Drafting in progress.
      </p>

